content.detailedDescription:
Saw a program on tv about the delphos, ks. case and thought this might be of interest to ted phillips.

this happened about 34 years ago, approximately 1973. i was about 15 at the time and was driving a tractor, farming in a field in very rural western kansas, about three miles north of beeler.  it was just after sundown, but it wasn't dark yet because i could still see dark shapes such as tree groves.  i was heading south, and as i came over a small rise, i could see down a draw about a half mile away, the trees of an abandonded farmstead.  in front of the grove of trees, on the ground, i observed what i can only describe as a circle of red flashing lights, similar to what would be seen if a group of about eight police cars were parked in a circle, and they all had the old style single "cherry" light on.  (to dispute the obvious, there weren't and still aren't that many cop cars in all of ness county, and why would they be parked in a circle, off a dirt road, in a pasture?).  i observed these red flashing lights for several minutes, through the front glass of the tractor, until i came to a corner and turned east, then i observed the same thing in the same place out the side glass, as i was driving parallel to it.  it did not appear to move, other than the flashing of the lights, and i could not see any solid object, as it was nearly dark, all i could see was the lights.  i continued to watch until i went over a rise and drove out of view.  as i went around back to the north end of the field, my father was there to relieve me, and of course i told him what i had seen, and where.  we were out of view of the farmstead at this time, and i can't remember if we had to fuel the tractor or how long we were stopped there, but after some time, he took off in the tractor and i proceded to the road.  when i got to the road, i had the choice of going south and driving to within 100 yards (from the road) of what i saw, or going north and going home.....I went north, fast.  i was very frightened and feared for my life.  i asked my dad the next day if he saw anything, and the answer was no.  i never returned to the location of the lights to see if i could spot imprints, scorch marks, etc., partly out of fear, ignorance of trace evidence, and assuming that since my dad didn't see anything, it probably wasn't there anymore.
   i am telling this story now, because of the program i saw about trace evidence, and maybe some of this evidence could still be there, after all these years.  i believe i can accurately estimate the location of what i saw because the trees are still there.  if you would like to persue this, or would like more information, i would be happy to help.  although i was raised in a rural setting, i have a b.S. degree in earth science and have been an air traffic controller for the past 20 years.  thank you for your time.
content.summary: Witnessed a circle of red flashing lights on the ground

We were roofing a house here in sitka
.  looked up and saw off in the distance what looked like the shape of a man very high near the clouds north of us.  my first thought was that someone was parachuting in since that happens here in the summers.  i was waiting to watch the parachutist drop into town but instead it went up and disappeared into the clouds.   minutes later it dropped out of clouds again and seemed to hover for a good thirty minutes.  i had time to go get binoculars and sight on it.  we all took turns watching through binoculars for thirty to forty minutes until it went far enough up and away that we could not see it anymore.  i could only explain it as looking like a balloon from the macy's parade that got away.

I was looking out of my living room window which faces n/ne observing the stars with my celestron binoculars. my eyes needed a break so i lowered the binoculars and was observing with eyes only. movement caught my eye when i focused on the location, observed a v formation of 7 craft with 3 or 4 more in a circular formation to left and 1 on the right flank between the first and second object, they looked like lightly glowing whitish grey ovals almos translucent like a jellyfish. said to my wife "holy sh.. they are flying in formation look, look." there they were moving towards me in a stright line about twice as fast as a commercial jetliner from the ne to sw,  i observed them for about 6-8 seconds then i could not see them any more they were over the house. i ran downstairs and out back to the deck with the binoculars to try and track them. it took about 3 seconds to get out back, i could not see them i lost them in the moonlight, the sky was pretty clear, small puffs of clouds (clouds were travelling n the opposite direction of the objects). the moon was very bright and was in the westeern sky. there was no noise what so ever, if it was human aircraft 7 or more they would have made some kind of noise. i live a few miles from philadelphia airport and know what planes look and sound like, and where they were flying i have never seen any planes take that path and i lived here for about twelve years.

1 no commercial aircraft travel in groups or formation
2 there were no blinking lights or beacons
3 no noise
4 was not birds or geese/no wings or heads/ travelling too fast for birds and also most of the birds have already gone south for the winter and birds typically do not fly at night. 
5 i am an avid skywatcher every night it is clear enough i use my telescope or binoculars. i have seen other uexplainable events in the sky but nothing like this.

content.detailedDescription:
I was coming over the 73 toll road (at the highest point) on the road. i looked straight ahead and saw a sphere-like shiney object in the sky. i watched it as i also kept my eye on the road for a good 5 minutes until the object entered a cloud. 

i continued watching the cloud while driving waiting for the object to reappear which never occurred. i compared the shape of the object to the airplanes which were arriving and departing at john wayne airport.  the airplane wings were visible and had no shine unlike the object. 

i called my wife when the object did not reappear and told her i had just seen a ufo. i couldn't believe it but at the same time i knew it wasn't a plane. by that time, i was already north bound on the 405 fwy. 

i did some research online hoping somebody had reported seeing something unusual on the same day but found nothing. when i discovered this site, i looked at photos from a previous sighting in orange county. i could not believe it when i saw the photo taken on 06/20/99--it was the exact object i had witnessed.
content.summary: Ufo over orange county, ca

content.detailedDescription: my boyfriend and i were driving home from wallingford to meriden using back roads going toward route 70. once we turned north onto old colony rd we noticed a fire ball in the sky above our car to our left. at first we thought it might be a meteor but the flight path was very level. i didn't appear to be falling from the sky but rather maintaining a course parallel to ours. it was fairly low in the sky, lower than a plane would fly. there is an air port pretty close to this area so out next notion was that it might be a plane in distress attempting to land at the air port. then the object passed over our car so it was now located on the right side of us, still driving north this is away from the air port and we quickly dismissed the thought that it may be a plane. now out of the trees in an more open view to our right it appeared to be just fire flying at least as fast as out car if not a little faster. there was no visible material to the object. no visible metal or rock just flames. once we go to route 70 we took a left hand turn and the object was still visible. we  took a right hand turn and parked in the parking lot of the aoh club and got out of the car and walked toward the back where the object was still visible. the object continued just past the back of the aoh and disappeared, it didn't fall or move up, it just disappeared. when we got home over the next couple of day i searched local news papers and news reports because i thought there would be some report of some sort of incident  related to this object. i found nothing, no plane crash no meteor, nothing related or indicating that anyone else had even witnessed this fire ball.
content.summary: Flying fire ball
